724741f-a.text: West street, Bethune, to West 12th Street. (Before Reconstruction). President Borough of Manhattan.
724741f-a.folder: West Street & Bethune Street, Manhattan, NY

724740f-b.text:
1. 469-485 West Street, a factory formerly used by the National Biscuit Company, east side, from Bethune Street to West 12th (formerly Troy) Street, opposite Pier 50, North River. April 18, 1931. P. L. Sperr.

2. The same at a later date,showing lengthier view of street and after the demolition or "L". May 12th, 1940. P. L. Sperr.
